Migration safety rules for a multi-dev team:

- Source of truth is migrations in git. Never rely on "it exists in Supabase already".
- Do not auto-run migrations on container boot unless user explicitly wants that behavior.
- If Alembic reports "multiple heads", use flask db heads + flask db merge to resolve, then commit the merge migration.
- If Alembic reports "can't locate revision", first check whether the migration file is missing from repo and needs to be committed/restored.
- Avoid database drift: do not instruct manual column/table changes in Supabase UI.
- Prefer the Supabase SESSION/TRANSACTION POOLER connection string (pooler.supabase.com), not direct db.<ref>.supabase.co when Docker networking is involved.
- For this Render live-test copy, commit and push any migration-order fixes before deploying so Render does not build from stale migration files.
- For free Render web services, do not rely on Render shell or pre-deploy commands. Run upgrade/seed/admin bootstrap locally against the dedicated live-test Supabase database before deploy.
- After live-test DB bootstrap, verify:
  - `flask db current` is at head
  - seed tables have expected row counts
  - at least one active admin user exists
